title: Understanding Data Cleaning
text: Data cleaning involves identifying and correcting errors or inconsistencies in a dataset to ensure it is accurate and ready for analysis.

title: Identifying Common Issues
text: Common issues in datasets include missing data, duplicate entries, and inconsistent data formats.

title: First Step in Data Cleaning
text: To visualize the data or run a model, the data needs to be processed so there are no gaps in the values.
